Greetings, everyone. Today, I want to share a few heartfelt words.

For the past half-year, I have around 50-70 miners have been consistently active in this subnet. However, since DTAO's launch, I've gradually shifted their focus to other subnets, leading to a steady decline in the number of miners. Now, the time has come for me to fully step away from mining this subnet.

I find it puzzling that while we aimed for decentralization, the subnet has always maintained a centralized scoring approach. Despite its long existence, nothing has really changed—though, to be fair, the scoring has remained consistent.

Regarding the open category, it was an interesting and unique idea within Bittensor. However, it seems that little effort has been dedicated to improving its reward mechanism. Simply adding more open categories without refining the reward system is almost meaningless. In particular, normalizing the open category scores within a narrow range (0.8 to 1) does little to highlight the real differences between miners.

The way incentives are distributed to validators is also problematic. Validators are often those with significant unstaked rather than miners. While this might be beneficial for your validators, it does little to reduce selling pressure, contrary to your claims (when miner incentives decrease, perhaps you could consider lowering the max volume as some form of gesture to support us)

Regarding model optimization, I share many of the same opts as the top miner who left before me. One additional point I’d like to make is that, for text-based models, your reward mechanism is quite lenient, allowing me to exploit tricks such as early termination during generation.

We could have done better. We could have gone further. We could have built something truly remarkable. Perhaps, if just a fraction of personal gain had been set aside, this community could have soared to new heights instead of facing such an end

## Introducing Nuance - The Incentive Layer for Global Discourse

In a world flooded with noise, Nuance exists to reward signal.

We're launching a new Bittensor subnet focused on elevating high-quality, thoughtful contributions on X.

### Vision

To build a transparent and decentralized incentive mechanism to power nuanced and factual conversation in social media, elevating knowledge and decreasing polarizing misinformation across the world.

### What sets Nuance apart
- It’s not about shouting the loudest — it’s about being the most useful.
- It’s transparent and trustless — your actions speak for you.
- We're not building another hype machine — we’re building a new layer of trusted communication, where aligned incentives power better public knowledge.

### How it works
Miners connect their uid to their X account, and get incentive based on how much engagement from specific trusted accounts they get on nuanced and factual posts.

Validation works like this:
1. The validator fetches the latest replies and quoted retweets of the miner's X account, powered by the Datura Desearch API.
2. The validator checks if any of the replies or quoted retweets are from accounts in a long list of over 400,000 trusted accounts. Only engagements from these accounts are counted to make it resilient to sybil attacks.
3. The validator checks if the post of the miner follow's the Nuance Constitution of being nuanced and factual, contributing to a more enlightened world. To do the checks nineteen.ai is used for inference.
4. The validator checks if the trusted accounts replies/quoted retweets are positive or negative.
5. The validator checks if the topic of conversation is Bittensor, in which case a small bonus is rewarded.
6. The validator updates the score of the miner.

Miners on Nuance aren’t just shilling or spamming — they’re rewarded for adding value to real conversations that matter. Whether it’s replying with insight to a trending post, explaining a complex topic clearly, or helping someone better understand Bittensor — Nuance sees it, scores it, and rewards it.

### Validators
Validators are encourage to update within 24 hours.

For the first 9 days burn of miner emission will gradually decrease from 90% to 0%, which should ensure initial high vtrust for both updated and not updated validators for the first few days.

To update please see instructions in the new repo:
https://github.com/NuanceNetwork/Nuance/blob/main/docs/validators.md

We are available to assist with any questions.

### Miners
Instructions for how to run miners are available at:
https://github.com/NuanceNetwork/Nuance/blob/main/docs/miners.md

What matters is real engagement on X, which can be achieved either through agents or through humans creating engagement from trusted accounts.

The list of trusted users and along with the constitution for which posts are evaluated on can be found at:

## Nuance Roadmap April-May

We’re building the next generation of our Nuance subnet to make decentralized social curation more powerful, scalable, and rewarding for high-quality contributions. Here's what's coming:


🐛 Today (already pushed) — Bug Fix
We’re resolving a bug that caused validator errors during engagement scoring due to a missing database field.

To protect the network’s vtrust and give validators time to update, 95% of emissions will be burned until Thursday, and then reduced to 70% until the update next Tuesday.

If everything runs smoothly, the burn will return to 0%.

---

### 🔍 April 29 — **Data API Launch**
We’re rolling out a public API that gives full transparency into how posts are being verified, scored, and rewarded.

Miners and users will be able to:
- See their post verifications and engagement scores
- Check if text passes our Nuance criteria
- Confirm if an account is verified

This makes it easy for anyone participating to understand how the system sees them — and how they can improve.

---

### 🧠 April 29 — **Category-Based Incentives**
Not all content is equal — and now, rewards won’t be either.

We’re moving to a category-based emission system:
- **40%** for posts about Bittensor
- **40%** for posts about Nuance
- **20%** for posts about everything else

Each category can have its own rules for what gets rewarded and how, enabling more tailored incentives for different types of discourse.

---

### ⭐ April 29 — **Engagement Ranking**
We’re adding an **engagement score** to verified users.

This score reflects an account’s influence — based on factors like follower count and activity — and scales how much their engagement is worth. Big voices matter more, and now they’ll count more too.

---

### 🔁 May 6 — **RT & QRT Support**
Replies already count toward engagement. Next up: **retweets and quote tweets**.

These will be added to our incentive model, rewarding a broader range of meaningful interactions.

---

### 🌐 May 6 — **Validator Submission API**
We’re making the network more scalable and inclusive.

With the new submission system:
- Validators can receive posts directly, no need to crawl all of X
- Users can link multiple handles to one UID

This unlocks a new level of scalability and makes mining accessible to everyday users outside of Bittensor.

## Nuance Major Update

After releasing the Nuance subnet MVP for a while, we have reached a stable state. Validators are now scoring miners correctly, and we're seeing miners getting incentives from sharing nuanced information on social platforms.

The MVP release aimed to support basic functions of the subnet, covering Twitter integration and fundamental processing flows including nuance checking and topic identification. However, being an MVP, it wasn't implemented with extensibility in mind - all processing logic relied heavily on a single file and method.

We've now formalized the codebase and separated concerns/logic into a well-structured architecture that is easier to maintain and extend:

- Modular Architecture: Restructured the codebase into distinct packages with clear responsibilities (social, processing, database, neurons)
- Improved Database Integration: Better data access with proper separation between domain and data layers (nuance/database/)
- Extensible Platform Support: Created a flexible framework for adding new social platforms beyond Twitter (nuance/social/discovery/)
- Composable Processing System: Developed a modular content analysis system that can be easily extended (nuance/processing/)
- Clean Separation of Concerns: Moved from a monolithic implementation to a component-based architecture. The validator now sit between components but it can be easily seperate to services when we need to think about performance once the subnet grows.
- For devs and miners who want to better understand our codebase, please check docs/devs for more documentation.

## New Features
Along with this architectural refactoring, we've also released new logic/features:

API Server for Validator Data Access: This serves as a gateway for client applications and subnet miners to view our validator's data to see how the subnet is performing. This will initially be set up on our owner's validator (neurons/validators/api_server).
Category-Weighted Scoring: Categories are now simply classified using topic tags, allowing for more nuanced reward distribution based on content categories. interaction score
Follower-Weighted Interaction Scoring: Interactions now provide more score if they are made by users with larger followings, creating better incentives for quality engagement. interaction score

### Validators
This update includes changes to validator setup. Validators, please review the updated setup instructions in `Nuance/docs/validators.md`. The changes include:

1. **Refine your .env files** – Ensure you provide the minimum required values, which now also include `WALLET_PATH`, `WALLET_NAME`, and `WALLET_HOTKEY`. You can refer to the example file `.env.example`.

2. **Update your Python environment with the new Nuance dependencies**:

```
uv sync
```
  
3. **Run Alembic migrations**:

```

```

4. **Start your validator as usual**:

```
pm2 start uv --name "validator_sn23" -- run python -m neurons.validator.main
```

This eliminates the need for a separate verification post if the miner only seeks scoring. For automatic scraping, account and verification post ID still need to be submitted on-chain.
- **Posts also rewarded, not only QRTs**: This means that a post that passes the nuance and topic check, by an account on the target list, can get rewarded, no need to QRT your own post.
- **Submission of interactions made easier**: now any uid can send interactions to validators, so that validators can pick them up and reward them. This means that non-technical miners can message us or other helpful validators/miners and we can submit their interactions for them so they get the rewards. Due to growth of posts, validators will no longer search and find all posts themselves, so this submission of interactions is important.
- **Improved Score Weighting for Verified Accounts**: Verified accounts now contribute increased scores for multiple engagements, while still respecting a capped model:
    - 1 engagement: 100%
    - 2 engagements: 170%
    - 3 engagements: 200%
    - 4+ engagements: capped at 200%

### Validators
Validators are encourage to update within 24 hours.

To update, simply run:

```
git pull
pm2 restart validator
```

Kindly check that your validator is not showing errors after updating.


### Miners
Miners will be required to submit interactions you get for validators to pick them up:
https://github.com/NuanceNetwork/Nuance/blob/main/examples/simple_submission.ipynb

Message us if you have questions. We are working on making a simple UI to do this.
